# Playwright UI Automation Framework

## Technology Stack

- Playwright
- TypeScript
- Node.js
- Page Object Model (POM)

## Features

- Clean and simple framework
- Reusable Page Objects
- Easy to maintain
- HTML reporting
- CI/CD ready

## Overview

This project contains automated UI tests for the Jupiter Toys application using **Playwright** and **TypeScript**.

**Application URL:**
http://jupiter.cloud.planittesting.com

The framework follows the **Page Object Model (POM)** to keep the code simple, reusable, and easy to maintain.

---

## Project Structure

```
PLANIT_AUTO_TEST
│
├── pages
│   ├── HomePage.ts
│   ├── ContactPage.ts
│   ├── ShopPage.ts
│   └── CartPage.ts
│
├── tests
│   ├── contact.spec.ts
│   ├── submit.spec.ts
│   └── cart.spec.ts
│
├── playwright.config.ts
├── package.json
├── tsconfig.json
├── Jenkinsfile
└── README.md
```

---

## Prerequisites

Make sure the following are installed:

- Node.js (v18.18.0)
- npm (9.8.1)

---

## Installation

Clone the repository:
npm
```bash
git clone <repository-url>
```

Go to the project folder:

```bash
cd PLANIT_AUTO_TEST
```

Install dependencies:

```bash
npm install
```

Install Playwright browsers:

```bash
npx playwright install
```

---

## Running Tests

Run all tests:

```bash
npx playwright test
```

Run a specific test file:

```bash
npx playwright test tests/contact.spec.ts
```

Run tests in headed mode:

```bash
npx playwright test --headed
```

Run tests using Chrome:

```bash
npx playwright test --project=chromium
```

---

## Test Cases

### Test Case 1

- Navigate to Contact page
- Click Submit without entering data
- Verify mandatory field validation messages
- Enter mandatory fields
- Verify validation messages disappear

---

### Test Case 2

- Navigate to Contact page
- Enter mandatory fields
- Submit the form
- Verify successful submission
- Test is executed **5 times** to ensure a 100% pass rate

---

### Test Case 3

- Purchase:
  - 2 Stuffed Frog
  - 5 Fluffy Bunny
  - 3 Valentine Bear
- Navigate to Cart
- Verify:
  - Product prices
  - Product subtotals
  - Cart total equals the sum of all subtotals

---

## Framework Design

This project uses:

- Playwright
- TypeScript
- Page Object Model (POM)

Each application page has its own class containing page actions and locators, making the framework easier to maintain and reuse.

---

## Reports

After execution, Playwright generates an HTML report.

To open the report:

```bash
npx playwright show-report
```

---

## CI/CD

The project can be integrated with Jenkins, GitHub Actions, or Azure DevOps by executing:

```bash
npm install
npx playwright install
npx playwright test
```

---

